Mark Marino <omar@osf.org> writes:

> The intention is that you combine your compression and then encryption in one
> program.  Less hassle, less mess. If anyone knows where to get it (I believe 
> it's called Pretty Good Privacy), do tell.

pgp is available on many ftp sites, such as gatekeeper.dec.com (16.1.0.2)
in /pub/micro/msdos/pgp/pgp10.zip. However it only runs on MSDOS and
requires a license to use the RSA patent.

If you only require a moderate amount of protection, you can use
zip which runs on Unix, VMS, MSDOS, OS/2:

     wuarchive.wustl.edu:/mirrors/misc/unix/zip10ex.zip
     wuarchive.wustl.edu:/mirrors/misc/unix/unzip41.tar-z
     pit-manager.mit.edu:/pub/zip/crypt/zipcrypt.shar (encryption code)

Non US residents must get the encryption code from Europe:
     garbo.uwasa.fi:/unix/arcers/zip10ex.zip
     garbo.uwasa.fi:/unix/arcers/unzip41.tar.Z.
     garbo.uwasa.fi:/pc/arcutil/zcrypt10.zip  (encryption code)

Jean-loup Gailly
